I prepared a [PR](https://github.com/PyGithub/PyGithub/pull/3181) with a potential fix, but here is another workaround for anyone who wants to keep their existing exception handling. A good place to put this might be your top-level `__init__.py`:

```python
from github import Requester, UnknownObjectException

_createException = Requester.Requester.createException

def createException(cls, status, headers, output):
    message = output.get("message", "").lower() if output is not None else ""
    if status == 404 and "no object found" in message:
        return UnknownObjectException(status, output, headers)
    else:
        return _createException(status, headers, output)

Requester.Requester.createException = createException
```

